Methods in java:
Method is a block of code in java that performs some action and it
may or may not return some data collection of statements that are grouped together
to perform an operation.

Example:
int add(int num1, int num2){
return num1+num2;
}

Benefits:
1)increases readability
2)easy modification
3) save memory
4) better organization

When should we use methods in iur code:
if more than 3 lines of code ...

